<BaseLayout title="Attis Insider — Explicit Studio">

  <article class="project-page">

    <div class="project-page__hero-image placeholder">
      Attis Insider — Hero Image
    </div>

    <h1 class="project-page__title">Attis Insider</h1>
    <p class="project-page__subtitle">Launched India's first biohacking community with a viral campaign and a bag of magic beans.</p>

    <div class="project-details">
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Client</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">Attis</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Industry</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">Biohacking / Wellness</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Services</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">Strategy, Campaign, Community</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Year</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">2024</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="project-details__label">Result</p>
        <p class="project-details__value">1000+ signups, &#8377;0 spent</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-page__label">The landscape</p>
    <p class="project-page__body">India's biohacking space was nonexistent. There were no dedicated brands, no communities, no cultural conversation around the idea that optimisation wasn't just for athletes or tech bros. Attis wanted to build a community before selling a product — but "biohacking" sounded intimidating.</p>

    <div class="project-page__full-image placeholder">
      Attis Insider — Image
    </div>

    <p class="project-page__label">The insight</p>
    <p class="project-page__body">We created Attis Insider — a membership-style community that made biohacking feel like a culture, not a science experiment. The launch campaign, "Magic Pills", was deliberately provocative: we sent mystery packages branded as pills to health influencers and content creators with no context.</p>

    <div class="project-page__full-image placeholder">
      Attis Insider — Image
    </div>
    <div class="project-page__image-grid">
      <div class="placeholder">Attis Insider — Image</div>
      <div class="placeholder">Attis Insider — Image</div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-page__label">The outcome</p>
    <p class="project-page__body">The campaign generated over 100k organic views, 500+ social mentions, and 1000+ community signups — all on &#8377;0 ad spend. The mystery packaging created FOMO-driven sharing loops that outperformed paid campaigns.</p>

